comments.text: V179D is a polymorphic accessory NNRTI-selected mutation. It contributes low-levels reductions in susceptibility to each of the NNRTIs. The combination of V179D and K103R act synergistically to reduce NVP and EFV susceptibility. V179D has a weight of 1.0 in the Tibotec ETR genotypic susceptibility score. V179E is a non-polymorphic mutation occasionally selected by NVP and EFV. V179E appears similar to V179D in its effects on NNRTIs. V179D/E do not appear to reduce the virological response to a first-line EFV-containing regimen.
